examples.en: It mists / it is misting.
The windows have misted up.
The hills were clothed in mist.
Her eyes misted over with tears.
The mist thickened.
The old castle was involved in mist.
A thick mist hung over the town.
The plant should be misted regularly.
Mist shrouded the castle.
The sun soon dispersed the mist.
When morning came, the mist had vanished away.
A dim mist shelled the god.
A mist filmed over the stars.
We could hardly see for the mist.
The light couldn't penetrate through the mist.
Mist rolled in from the sea.
A cotton wool mist descended.
As the sun got hotter, it sucked up the mist from the sea.
It was misting when we arrived.
The windshield misted over.
The view was obscured by mist.
The cliff was shrouded in mist.
Thick mist clouded the mountaintops.
The mountains were wreathed in mist.
The plant has to be misted every day.
The hills were veiled in a fine mist.
We could barely make out some figures moving in the mist.
The grassy hills were sheathed in mist.
The river was sliding darkly under the mist.
Mist eddied round the house.
